TASK_ID=37
TASK_TITLE=Fast freelancer spawn — premade 3x2 team with one-click launch
TASK_STATUS=in_progress
TASK_CREATED=1743350400
TASK_TYPE=infrastructure
TASK_DESCRIPTION=The "Spawn Freelancer" flow is too slow and clunky. It needs to be instant and smooth — one click from the TUI Quick Action card or one command, and 6 freelancers are up in seconds.

THREE DELIVERABLES:

1. PREMADE TEAM DEFINITION — Create a freelancer.team.md (or similar) that defines the reserved 3x2 freelancer pool as a first-class team type. Grid: 3 columns x 2 rows = 6 freelancers. No manager pane — all 6 are independent workers. This definition should be the single source of truth for what "Spawn Freelancer" means. The team def should specify: grid (3x2), model (opus), team type (freelancer), layout preferences, and any default agent/system-prompt to use.

2. FAST LAUNCH PATH — Rewrite/optimize the spawn sequence so it completes in under 5 seconds wall time (not counting Claude boot). Current flow: parse grid → create window → split panes one-by-one → name panes → write team env → update session env → launch Claude in each pane sequentially (with 0.5s sleeps) → apply layout → verify boot. Optimizations needed: (a) Batch pane creation — split all at once or use a faster approach than sequential split-window. (b) Remove unnecessary sleeps or reduce them to minimum. (c) Launch all Claude instances in rapid succession (no 0.5s inter-pane sleep — tmux can handle it). (d) Apply layout immediately after splits, not after launches. (e) Write team env and session env in parallel with launches. (f) The skill file (.claude/skills/doey-add-window/) should have a fast-path for --freelancer that skips unnecessary steps (no manager setup, no agent assignment, simpler naming). Consider a dedicated /doey-spawn-freelancers skill that is purpose-built for this one action.

3. TUI INTEGRATION — The Quick Action "Spawn Freelancers" button (task 35) sends a command to Boss. Make sure whatever command it sends triggers the optimized fast path. The button label should say "Spawn Freelancers" (plural). When clicked, the user should see freelancers appearing almost immediately — the UX should feel instant.

CONSTRAINTS:
- Must work on fresh install (no pre-existing team files or env vars)
- Bash 3.2 compatible
- Grid is always 3x2 for freelancers (not configurable via this path — power users can still use /doey-add-window with custom grids)
- One worker per file rule applies to implementation
TASK_TAGS=infrastructure,shell,skills,tui,teams
TASK_TEAM=W2
